  "text": "This is a form of the action for an (m, n) string. It is related to the F1 action by an S-duality transformation from (1, 0) to (m, n), and can be obtained from the usual D1 action by integrating out the Born-Infeld vector [CITATION_1] . We see that for (m, n) = (1, 0) we immediately get the F1 action, while for (m, n) = (0, 1) we get an action with tension",
