  "bib_entries": {
    "15038478": {
      "title": "D-brane actions",
      "abstract": "Abstract Effective world-brane actions for solitons of ten-dimensional type IIA and IIB superstring theory are derived using the formulation of solitons as Dirichlet branes. The one-brane actions are used to recover predictions of SL(2, Z ) strong-weak coupling duality. The two-brane action, which contains a hidden eleventh target-space coordinate, is shown to be the eleven-dimensional supermembrane action. It can be thought of as the membrane action of “M-theory”."
    }
